texts.text: Their numbers are getting ridiculous!
>No matter how many you kill, more arrive.
>The fight is gradually building towards the point where you'll get overrun by the enemy.
We're gonna get overrun before we can get away!
What's your plan now?!
Just keep running!
Don't look back!
Don't look back!
I AM running!
It's just these people are slower than I thought...!
I can't help it!
Am I supposed to just ignore all the screaming demons coming after me?!
>Assaulted by an endless barrage of enemy attacks, it is all you can do just to keep the prisoners safe.
>You manage to ward off the attacks, but in that instant,

*Pant*
Whoa!
>The girl just in front of you trips and falls...
No! My daughter!
Dammit...!
Piece of cake!
I'll handle it!
>You quickly pick up the girl and rejoin the group.
Thank you!
>Just as you are making sure the girl is able to keep up with the others,
>you feel a sharp pain in your ankle.
[sys user_name], you're hurt!
Just keep moving!
Don't mind me!
Don't mind me!
I'd do it if I could,
but you're all I got right now!
No!
I can't do this without you!
Everybody just keep running!
Move it people! Don't forget why we're doing this!
>At the sound of Pixie's shouts, the prisoners start moving again.
C'mon! Summon some demons! Do I have to do everything for you?!
>You finish summoning before she can finish the sentence.
>But it is futile against the incoming onslaught.
>It isn't long before you are overwhelmed...
Where am I...?
I'm alive...?
You're up! Resilient sombitch aren't ya?
Somebody go tell the boss that the Downloader's awake!
>You find yourself in a lavishly furnished hall.
>Pixie is nowhere to be seen.
>Instead you are surrounded by the demons who visited Yotsuya city.
You're packing some pretty sweet gear here. You're not just some random summoner are ya?
>The demon has your Armaments and smartphone.
Don't even bother trying to struggle.
You Downloaders ain't nothing without this stuff,
no matter how good you are.
The Downloader's awake?
This way boss.
So, you're the Downloader who's been helping the people of Yotsuya city.
I have no relations to them.
Still acting tough huh? It makes no difference whether you talk or not you know?
You're a fool then. Only fools risk their lives for complete strangers.
Either way, it doesn't matter now. You're our new hostage.
I'm nothing to them.
I'm nothing to them.
Holding me hostage is meaningless.
Let's see if they think the same.
We'll see by how they react to this.
>The screen in the hall is turned on to show the image of a place.
>By the makeshift walls of metal scraps covered in rags, you can tell it is Yotsuya city.
Come out, humans!
What do you want?
>A bunch of Dx2s poke their head out, including Akito.
We have the Downloader that helped you escape!
Y-You mean alive?
>Your eyes meet Akito's through the screen. It looks to be a live transmission.
As you can see, yes. But this one challenged our reign, and that is a grave offense.
That's why we will be holding an execution tomorrow!
What?!
You...! You're the first one that escaped right? Well listen to me real hard.
If you want to save your friend, bring back all the hostages to us.
If even one of them doesn't turn up, we'll make an example out of your friend.
So act wisely.
>The people of Yotsuya city are left speechless by the demon's message.
>Your eyes meet Akito's one more time
>as the screen goes dark.
What do you think?
They'll make their escape.
You really think they'll come back?
A pessimist, eh?
I know that you humans have been through a lot,
but you really should learn to have more faith in people.
Who knows?
But if they really meant to abandon you, they should be gone by now.
And if they do decide to leave, I'll just send my minions after them.
See you tomorrow then,
Downloader with a hero complex.

*Groan*
Whoa... I...
I must've gotten knocked out by that blast...
Wait! [sys user_name]!
Where...? OMG, did they...?!
Goddammit, what would that idiot do without me!
